subsection.content:
a description of the subject matter and nature of
                    the investigation, prosecution, offence or criminal matter and whether or not
                    proceedings have been instituted;

information on the identity and location of any
                    person to be served, that person’s relationship to the proceedings, and the
                    manner in which service is to be made;

information as to the allowances and expenses to
                    which any person asked to appear in the Requesting Party will be
                    entitled;

any court order, or a certified copy thereof,
                    sought to be enforced and a statement to the effect that it is a final
                    order;

the request for assistance relates to an offence
                    that is regarded by the Requested Party as an offence of a political
                    character;

the Requesting Party cannot comply with any
                    conditions in relation to confidentiality or limitation as to the use of
                    material provided;

the acts or omissions alleged to constitute the
                    offence would not, if they had taken place within the jurisdiction of the
                    Requested Party, have constituted an offence;

the totality of the acts or omissions alleged to
                    constitute the offence against the law of the Requesting Party shall be
                    considered and not merely the legal elements of that offence;

the receiving Party shall have the obligation to
                    keep the person transferred in custody unless otherwise authorised by the
                    sending Party;

the receiving Party shall return the person
                    transferred to the custody of the sending Party as soon as circumstances permit,
                    unless otherwise agreed by both Parties and the person transferred;
